Yes. Since your existing `sales_points` table already has the old structure, for local/dev easiest is **drop and recreate**.

Use this final model:

```text
users/person
   ↓
person_sales_point_relationships
   ↓
sales_points
```

## 1. Liquibase: drop old table and recreate

Create a new changelog file, for example:

```text
004-rebuild-sales-points-model.yaml
```

```yaml
databaseChangeLog:
  - changeSet:
      id: 004-drop-old-sales-points-table
      author: rahul
      preConditions:
        - onFail: MARK_RAN
        - tableExists:
            tableName: sales_points
      changes:
        - dropTable:
            tableName: sales_points
            cascadeConstraints: true

  - changeSet:
      id: 005-create-sales-points-table
      author: rahul
      changes:
        - createTable:
            tableName: sales_points
            columns:
              - column:
                  name: id
                  type: BIGINT
                  autoIncrement: true
                  constraints:
                    primaryKey: true
                    nullable: false

              - column:
                  name: sales_point_id
                  type: VARCHAR(100)
                  constraints:
                    nullable: false
                    unique: true

              - column:
                  name: label
                  type: VARCHAR(200)
                  constraints:
                    nullable: false

  - changeSet:
      id: 006-create-person-sales-point-relationships-table
      author: rahul
      changes:
        - createTable:
            tableName: person_sales_point_relationships
            columns:
              - column:
                  name: id
                  type: BIGINT
                  autoIncrement: true
                  constraints:
                    primaryKey: true
                    nullable: false

              - column:
                  name: person_user_id
                  type: VARCHAR(100)
                  constraints:
                    nullable: false

              - column:
                  name: sales_point_id
                  type: VARCHAR(100)
                  constraints:
                    nullable: false

              - column:
                  name: relationship_type
                  type: VARCHAR(20)
                  constraints:
                    nullable: false

              - column:
                  name: org_unit_id
                  type: VARCHAR(100)
                  constraints:
                    nullable: false
```

